dxMIB.name: dxMIB
dxMIB.description: This module contains eTrust Directory-specific SNMP information.

dxMWTable.name: dxMWTable
dxMWTable.description: The table holding information relating to the MW status of remote DSAs.

dxMWEntry.name: dxMWEntry
dxMWEntry.description: Entry containing information relating to the MW status of remote DSAs.

dxMWIndex.name: dxMWIndex
dxMWIndex.description: Create a unique key to identify rows of MW information

dxRemoteDsaName.name: dxRemoteDsaName
dxRemoteDsaName.description: Name of the current Remote DSA

dxMWQueueLength.name: dxMWQueueLength
dxMWQueueLength.description: The number of currently MWs outstanding

dxMWStatus.name: dxMWStatus
dxMWStatus.description: Status of MW queue. The meaning of the statuses are as follows: internal-error - An internal error has occurred. ok - MW is functioning correctly. failed - The MW DSA is not contactable. Update will be queued. The uncontactable DSA needs attention. failed-no-dsa - MW Update failed. Knowledge of DSA lost. non-existent - Waiting for DISP but knowledge of DSA lost. recovering - MW DSA has been contacted and being updated. disp-failed - A failure occurred during DISP. The cause of this needs to be resolved before MW will continue. wait-disp - Waiting for DISP to complete before MWing. q-purged - MW queue was purged and MW to the DSA disabled. failed-sent - Have sent an update to a previously uncontactable DSA and waiting on a response.

dxMWPendingRemote.name: dxMWPendingRemote
dxMWPendingRemote.description: Gauge of pending remote MW operations

dxMWConfirmedLocal.name: dxMWConfirmedLocal
dxMWConfirmedLocal.description: Gauge of queued MW operations that have been applied locally.

dxStatsNilCredit.name: dxStatsNilCredit
dxStatsNilCredit.description: The number of times flow control was applied to any association

dxStatsNoTicks.name: dxStatsNoTicks
dxStatsNoTicks.description: The number of times in the last minute processing did not occur NOTE: This requires stats logging/tracing to enable

dxStatsBusy.name: dxStatsBusy
dxStatsBusy.description: The percentage of time in the last minute the DSA was busy NOTE: This requires stats logging/tracing to enable

dxStatsOps.name: dxStatsOps
dxStatsOps.description: The total number of operations processed since DSA was started

dxStatsEntries.name: dxStatsEntries
dxStatsEntries.description: The total number of entries returned since DSA was started

dxStatsMWQ.name: dxStatsMWQ
dxStatsMWQ.description: The number of queued multiwrite operations

dxCacheStatus.name: dxCacheStatus
dxCacheStatus.description: Status of DxCache. The meaning of the statuses are as follows: internal-error - An internal error has occurred. cache-disabled - DxCache is disabled (see trace log if unexpected): - Not turned on - Had a problem loading - Had a problem during an entry update - Has exceeded the maximum configured size - Machine has run out of memory - etc etc cache-building - DxCache is currently loading information from the backend. cache-ok - DxCache is up and running. cache-dirty - The DSA has received a DISP update. DxCache will be refreshed

dxCacheSize.name: dxCacheSize
dxCacheSize.description: Memory in (mb) currently being used by DxCache.

dxCacheSearchHits.name: dxCacheSearchHits
dxCacheSearchHits.description: Number of search requests serviced by DxCache.

dxCacheSearchMisses.name: dxCacheSearchMisses
dxCacheSearchMisses.description: Number of search requests going through to the backend.

dxCacheSequentialScans.name: dxCacheSequentialScans
dxCacheSequentialScans.description: Number of searches requiring a sequential scan of the cache.
